The paper focuses on the calibration of a cable-driven robotic surgical assistant using RGBD sensing and machine learning techniques. This falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV) as the RGBD sensing is used to track the fiducial coordinate frame. The use of machine learning techniques such as recurrent neural networks and linear models suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the fact that the robotic assistant is used in a surgical setting suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
